INTRODUCTION: Treatment of pediatric malignancies is becoming progressively more 
complex, implying the adoption of multimodal therapies. A reliable, long-lasting 
venous access represents one of the critical requirements for the success of 
those treatments. Recent technical innovations-such as minimally invasive 
procedures for placement, new devices and novel materials-have rapidly spread 
