been discussed and formulated.
CONCLUSIONS: The importance of the correct choice, management and use of VADs in 
pediatric oncohematological patients is a necessary prerequisite for an adequate 
standard of care, also considering the increased chances of cure and the longer 
life expectancy of those patients with modern therapies.

